<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
    Sparkle appcast for Draught (the writing surface).

    Served at: https://procestra.app/appcast-draught.xml
    (Draught's SUFeedURL in Info.plist points here. On launch the app GETs
    this file and compares each <sparkle:version> against the installed
    CFBundleVersion; a higher number triggers an update prompt.)

    STATUS: Draught is not released yet. This feed is STAGED and intentionally
    has NO <item> — Sparkle sees nothing newer, so no update is ever offered.
    That's correct until the first public build ships.

    Signing key: Draught shares the suite EdDSA key pair by design.
    SUPublicEDKey (in Draught's Info.plist) = moOo7kLO86SRjjyTWlHabtgP0ep5ECR7biu30ZmTwEQ=
    (Seed / Provenance / Espalier use the same key — this is intentional.)

    To ship the first version: add an <item> below with sparkle:version (the
    integer build), shortVersionString, minimumSystemVersion, a release-note
    <description>, and an <enclosure> pointing at the DMG on R2 with the
    edSignature + length from sign_update:

        .build/artifacts/sparkle/Sparkle/bin/sign_update build/Draught-<v>.dmg
        → prints sparkle:edSignature="…" length="…"

    then deploy this file. See ../Provenance/RELEASE.md for the runbook.
-->
<rss version="2.0"
     xmlns:sparkle="http://www.andymatuschak.org/xml-namespaces/sparkle"
     xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">
    <channel>
        <title>Draught</title>
        <link>https://procestra.app/draught.html</link>
        <description>Updates for Draught, the writing surface.</description>
        <language>en</language>

        <item>
            <title>Version 1.0.0</title>
            <pubDate>Thu, 17 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>1</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>1.0.0</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <!-- 14.0, NOT 13.0: Draught builds against the macOS 14 SDK floor.
                 A 13.0 value would offer macOS 13 users a build that can't
                 launch (the appcast min-OS trap). -->
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <description><![CDATA[
                <h2>Draught 1.0.0</h2>
                <p>The writing surface: a stupidly simple prose and screenplay
                app that quietly remembers everything and exports beautifully.</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><b>A calm page</b> — a centered reading column on a quiet sheet, a block caret, and nothing else.</li>
                  <li><b>Screenplay lens</b> — Fountain formatting that falls out of typing; the file stays plain text.</li>
                  <li><b>Quiet memory</b> — projects keep every version; history, scraps, and notes are one click away.</li>
                  <li><b>Beautiful exports</b> — Reading, Manuscript, Book, and Screenplay PDFs.</li>
                </ul>
            ]]></description>
            <!-- TODO(sign-at-release): edSignature + length come from
                 sign_update over the FINAL signed/notarized DMG:
                 .build/artifacts/sparkle/Sparkle/bin/sign_update build/Draught-1.0.0.dmg -->
            <enclosure
                url="https://pub-db9995825af14961a74cb646cccf5ac2.r2.dev/draught-downloads/Draught-1.0.0.dmg"
                sparkle:edSignature="SIGN-AT-RELEASE"
                length="0"
                type="application/octet-stream" />
        </item>
    </channel>
</rss>
